# Optimized Supply Chain Regression Analysis

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project performs a **Multiple Linear Regression (MLR)** analysis on a global supply chain dataset to identify how key supply chain variables affect **sales performance per customer**.  
The optimized version of the script keeps only essential variables, applies preprocessing, runs regression with **statsmodels**, and exports results to Excel.  

## ğŸ› ï¸ Tools & Libraries Used
- **Python 3**
- **Pandas** â†’ Data preprocessing & cleaning  
- **Statsmodels** â†’ Regression analysis (OLS)  
- **ExcelWriter (pandas)** â†’ Export results to Excel  

## ğŸ“Š Analysis & Workflow
1. **Data Selection** â€“ Focused on essential features (Sales, Quantity, Price, Discount, Shipping Days, Delivery Risk, Customer/Market Segments).  
2. **Aggregation** â€“ Grouped by `Customer Id` with meaningful aggregation (sum for sales, mean for shipping days, etc.).  
3. **Encoding** â€“ Applied **one-hot encoding** to categorical variables (Delivery Status, Customer Segment, Market, Category Name).  
4. **Regression Model** â€“ Fitted **OLS regression** using statsmodels.  
5. **Output** â€“ Exported coefficients, p-values, R-squared, F-statistic, and significant variables to Excel.  

## ğŸ“ˆ Outputs
- **Regression Coefficients** (with t-stats & p-values)  
- **Model Metrics** (R-squared, Adjusted R-squared, F-statistic, Significance F)  
- **Significant Variables (p < 0.05)** highlighted in console  

